<plot>Situation comedy--with music--was set at the turn of the century. It's main focus and synopsis was about two Broadway song publishers (Bob Haymes and Leo DeLyon) . They had plenty of opportunities to demonstrate their wares (grand old favorites--like "After the Ball"), as well as to welcome visiting vaudevillians to their office. The show co-starred the beloved Dorothy Loudon as the two song publishers' secretary.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?270501</url></doc>
